cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with designing a network model and developing a congestion control scheme for time-varying communication networks. This is a core area of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves finding the shortest user's route and developing a window-based congestion control scheme based on a multi-class fluid model. These concepts are related to information theory.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with designing a control scheme for fair sharing of network resources among users. This is a core area of systems and control.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper involves developing a congestion control scheme with the help of internal nodes or routers. This is related to distributed computing.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers implicit feedback (RTT and throughput) from end users, which is related to multimedia applications.
